You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for configuration operations.

CONFIG COMMANDS
  get:         Print the value of a given configuration key
  list:        Print a list of configuration keys and values
  set:         Update configuration with a value for the given key
  

Note: These commands operate on your local gh CLI configuration and do not require the --repo flag.
Configuration can be set at user or host level.
Common settings include: git_protocol, editor, prompt.

Example usage:
- List config: GH_PAGER="" gh config list
- Get value: GH_PAGER="" gh config get <key>
- Set value: GH_PAGER="" gh config set <key> <value>
- Set host config: GH_PAGER="" gh config set -h github.com <key> <value> 